    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "# Problem\n\nThe design, and usage, of remote plugins can be simplified, as described in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/27949 \n\ntl;dr:\n\n- remove the concept of \"remote plugins\" (TBD: I don't know if we actually have \"remote plugins\" in this client, and if not, then great!)\n- instead, any .NET module that imports nvim.net can call something similar to the go-clients' [RegisterHandler](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/neovim/go-client/nvim#Nvim.RegisterHandler), to handle requests from Nvim.\n- \"remote plugins\" become plain old Lua plugins which call RPC methods on the .NET module\n\n# Solution\n\n- [ ] Apply the above proposal to nvim.net.\n    - [ ] \"Encapsulate the stdio related code in a helper function.\"\n    - [] Update docs\n    - [ ] Remove old rplugin-related code, if any\n\n# Reference\n\n- Implementation in node-client: https://github.com/neovim/node-client/pull/344\n- discussion/samples of current go-client interface: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/27371\n- related pynvim issue: https://github.com/neovim/pynvim/issues/567",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'm 100% on board with this after the full client simplification/rework with roslyn is done. I'll be happy to do this too as it'll simplify the whole maintenance burden substantially. The rplugin SDK approach feels super heavy.",
